    GetTupleIndexer(Type)

    Retrieves the indexer for type of Tuple specified.

    Declaration
    public static Func<object, int, object> GetTupleIndexer(this Type tupleType)
    Parameters
    Type Name Description
    Type tupleType

    The type of the tuple.
    Returns
    Type Description
    Func<Object, Int32, Object>

    The indexer (as a function) for the tupleType specified
    Remarks

    Supports standard tuple extension, where TRest is itself a Tuple.

    For example index 7 (indices are zero-indexed so that is the 8th item) of a tuple of type: Tuple<int, int, int, int, int, int, int, Tuple<string>> is the equivalent of tuple.Rest.Item1 and is of type String.

    The item at index 7 of a tuple of type Tuple<int, int, int, int, int, int, int, string> is the equivalent of tuple.Rest and is of type String.

    View Source
